    <string name="desc_enable_candidate_variant_first">
        Prefers Traditional Chinese characters first
        over the default of showing Simplified Chinese characters first.
    </string>
    <string name="desc_disable_user_input_data">
        Prevents analyzing the input to prevent privacy leaks.
        However, it will reduce the
        word matching accuracy of the input method.
    </string>
    <string name="desc_enable_x_input_pad">
        If the X-shaped keyboard is enabled,
        an input mode similar to the 8VIM/8pen-system will be used
        to support continuous input of Pinyin and Latin characters.
    </string>
    <string name="desc_enable_latin_use_pinyin_keys_in_x_input_pad">
        Enabling this option aligns the Latin keyboard layout with the Pinyin keyboard,
        minimizing discomfort when switching between the two.
        However, it may slightly reduce efficiency for English input.
    </string>
    <string name="desc_adapt_desktop_swipe_up_gesture">
        If the system uses a swipe-up gesture to return to the home screen,
        this settings adds a blank space beneath the input keyboard
        to prevent conflicts between swipe input and the system swipe-up gesture.
    </string>

